The abbot lets for fifteen years from the fest of the coapostolis Philippi et Jacobi nyxt and immediat follouand to Petir Ramsay and his wife Isobell Barre and their affignees of no higher degree the teindsheaves of the church of Monyfuth except the teindiheaves of the mains of the Grange belonging to the parsonage—and the vicarage kirkland and glebe of the same—paying yearly for the parsonage 4 chalders of wheat, 9 chalders 3 bolls of bear, and 12 chalders 11 bolls of meal, becauys that the lard of Grange teynd schawys ar defalkyt and of strikyn in the haill wictualis--and for the vicarage 40 marks of money and 4 barrels of salmon. The abbot also lets to the same parties his fishing of the Portyn-

crag for the same period——they paying yearly 10 barrels of salmon. 18 April 1531.
